Here's the enhanced spec for CC:

---

## Enhancement Part 2: Agent Access in Templates

**Goal:** Allow templates to include `agent_access` field that can be set at creation time, making permission management part of the natural creation workflow.

### Template Enhancement

Templates can now include `{{AGENT_ACCESS}}` placeholder in frontmatter:

```markdown
---
title: "{{TITLE}}"
created: "{{DATE}}"
agent_access: "{{AGENT_ACCESS}}"
---

# {{TITLE}}

{{CONTENT}}
```

### Natural Language Inference

When `create_note_from_template` is called, infer `agent_access` level from user's language:

**"full" access triggers:**
- "you can edit"
- "you can update"
- "fully editable"
- "you can modify"

**"append" access (default):**
- "you can add to"
- "append-only"
- No specific instruction (use "append" as safe default)

**"none" access:**
- "read-only"
- "I'll edit this myself"
- "just create it"

### Updated Tool Signature

**`create_note_from_template`** - Add optional parameter:
```typescript
{
  template: string,
  output_filename: string,
  fields: { [key: string]: string },
  agent_access?: "full" | "append" | "none"  // NEW
}
```

**Parameter behavior:**
- If `agent_access` explicitly provided → use it
- Else if template has `{{AGENT_ACCESS}}` → infer from natural language
- Else if template has hardcoded value → keep template's value
- Else → use "append" as safe default

### Example Workflows

**User:** "Create a reference doc about my mechanical keyboards that you can fully edit"

**CC calls:**
```typescript
create_note_from_template({
  template: "REFERENCE_DOC.md",
  output_filename: "mechanical-keyboards-reference.md",
  fields: {
    TITLE: "Mechanical Keyboards Reference",
    OVERVIEW: "A collection of details about my keyboard collection",
    AGENT_ACCESS: "full"  // inferred from "you can fully edit"
  }
})
```

**Result:**
```markdown
---
title: "Mechanical Keyboards Reference"
created: "2026-03-24"
agent_access: "full"
---

# Mechanical Keyboards Reference

## Overview
A collection of details about my keyboard collection

## Details
[Claude can now edit this section directly]
```

### Template Library Updates

Update example templates to include the placeholder:

**JOURNAL.md:**
```markdown
---
date: "{{DATE}}"
agent_access: "append"
---
```
(Journals are typically append-only)

**REFERENCE_DOC.md:**
```markdown
---
title: "{{TITLE}}"
agent_access: "{{AGENT_ACCESS}}"
---
```
(Reference docs often need editing)

**MEETING_NOTES.md:**
```markdown
---
title: "{{TITLE}}"
date: "{{DATE}}"
agent_access: "full"
---
```
(Meeting notes often need updating)

